  "texts": [
    "Then since x ′ ̸ ⊑ θ(φ) is equivalent to M p, x ′ ⊮ φ by the inductive hypothesis, the right side of the previous 'iff' is equivalent to M p, x ⊩ ¬φ.",
    "For the □ i case, θ(□ i φ) = ■ i θ(φ), so we show that M p, x ⊩ □ i φ iff x ⊑ ■ i θ(φ).",
    "From left to right, suppose x ̸ ⊑ ■ i θ(φ), so x ∧ ♦ i -θ(φ) ̸ = ⊥.",
    "Then since A is a V-BAO and hence an R-BAO by Lemma 5.13, there is a y ∈ A such that ⊥ ̸ = y ⊑ -θ(φ) and xR i y.",
    "Hence y ̸ ⊑ θ(φ), which with the inductive hypothesis implies M p, y ⊮ φ, which with xR i y implies M p, x ⊮ □ i φ."
